From 9c2790d955ded0afa893f924b5831b9d2f95ca94 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mingcong Bai <jeffbai@aosc.io>
Date: Fri, 15 May 2026 16:21:40 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 568/587] AOSCOS: drm: cix: fix build error with
 -Werror=misleading-indentation
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Whilst building with CONFIG_WERROR enabled, the following error occurs:

  drivers/gpu/drm/cix/linlon-dp/linlondp_dev.c: In function ‘linlondp_dev_create’:
  drivers/gpu/drm/cix/linlon-dp/linlondp_dev.c:655:5: error: this ‘if’ clause does not guard... [-Werror=misleading-indentation]
    655 |     if (err)
        |     ^~
  drivers/gpu/drm/cix/linlon-dp/linlondp_dev.c:658:9: note: ...this statement, but the latter is misleadingly indented as if it were guarded by the ‘if’
    658 |         is_insmod = linlondp_gop_get();
        |         ^~~~~~~~~

Fix the indentation around this statement to address the warning.

Fixes: "CIXTECH: drm: add cix linlon dp driver"
Link: https://github.com/cixtech/cix-linux-main/issues/26
Signed-off-by: Mingcong Bai <jeffbai@aosc.io>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/cix/linlon-dp/linlondp_dev.c | 6 +++---
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/cix/linlon-dp/linlondp_dev.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/cix/linlon-dp/linlondp_dev.c
index 91b2b8ecae3ce..8abc6c98c1573 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/cix/linlon-dp/linlondp_dev.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/cix/linlon-dp/linlondp_dev.c
@@ -650,10 +650,10 @@ struct linlondp_dev *linlondp_dev_create(struct device *dev)
 
 	mdev->dev = dev;
 
-    err = device_property_read_u32(dev, "enabled_by_gop",
+	err = device_property_read_u32(dev, "enabled_by_gop",
                                (u32 *)&mdev->enabled_by_gop);
-    if (err)
-        mdev->enabled_by_gop = 0;
+	if (err)
+        	mdev->enabled_by_gop = 0;
 
 	is_insmod = linlondp_gop_get();
 	if (is_insmod)
-- 
2.52.0

